{"serial": "09012", "department_serial": 3, "code": "GS3065", "class": "*", "name": {"en": "Literacy of digital communication and critical thinking", "ch": "數位傳播素養與批判思考"}, "notice": {"en": "", "ch": ""}, "instructor": {"en": ["Yang-Yi,Zheng"], "ch": ["鄭揚宜"]}, "credits": 2, "time_loc": [{"time": {"week": 1, "session": ["5", "6"]}, "loc": {"building": "O", "room": "214"}}], "isRequired": false, "isFullSem": false, "MaxStu": 50, "department": {"ch": "通識教育中心", "en": "General Education Center"}, "system": {"ch": "學士班", "en": "Undergraduate Programme"}, "language": {"ch": "國語", "en": "Chinese"}, "card": {"ch": "部份使用", "en": "Optional"}, "assigned": 26, "selected": 48, "remark": {"ch": "", "en": ""}, "goal": {"ch": "本課程的設計目的，在於理解當代數位傳播對於大腦、思考、人類行為、社會影響、文化認知與國族建構的過程；理解自我在數位科技、社群媒體影響下的改變與發展，如何影響自我的認知、閱讀行為、社群交往、資訊生產與使用；理解當代數位科技與社群媒體影響下各種行銷、內容生產、機器人、假訊息、置入性行銷、網紅、網軍、帶風向等產業與現象；學習如何檢視數位工具防止假訊息的危害、判讀事實與進行事實查詢；學習如何批判與監督媒體；學習如何參與與實踐公民討論與民主實踐，達成數位傳播素養的培育與培力。", "en": "The design objective of this course is to comprehend the processes through which contemporary digital communication impacts the brain, cognition, human behavior, societal influences, cultural perception, and national identity construction. It aims to understand how the self changes and develops under the influence of digital technology and social media, impacting self-perception, reading behaviors, social interactions, information production, and usage. The course also aims to grasp various industries and phenomena influenced by contemporary digital technology and social media, such as marketing, content production, robotics, misinformation, product placement, influencers, online manipulation groups, and trend shaping.\n\nStudents will learn how to examine digital tools to prevent the harm caused by misinformation, discern facts, and conduct fact-checking. Moreover, they‘ll delve into critical analysis and oversight of media platforms, participate in and practice citizen discussions, and engage in democratic practices. Ultimately, the course seeks to cultivate and empower digital literacy, enabling individuals to critically evaluate, participate in, and contribute to discussions and democratic practices in digital communication."}, "outline": {"ch": "第一週    課程介紹\n第二週    真相是什麼？形上學和知識論進路\n第三週    想像的共同體：傳播模式與國族認同\n第四週    注意力商人：數位傳播與市場行銷\n第五週    如何上癮：社群平台如何影響我們的生活\n第六週    假新聞與他們的產地\n第七週    種瓜得豆：內容農場\n第八週    與論操縱與口碑行銷\n第九週    事實查核的工具與方法\n第十週    鄉民與鍵盤俠：失控的匿名正義\n第十一週   地緣政治與資訊戰\n第十二週   直播、網紅與梗圖\n第十三週   數位平台該不該管、該怎麼管？\n第十四週   公共媒體與優質媒體\n第十五週   期末成果報告\n第十六週   期末成果報告", "en": "Week 1: Course Introduction\nWeek 2: What is Truth? Metaphysical and Epistemological Approaches\nWeek 3: Imagined Communities: Communication Patterns and National Identity\nWeek 4: Attention Merchants: Digital Communication and Market Marketing\nWeek 5: How to Get Addicted: How Social Platforms Influence Our Lives\nWeek 6: Fake News and Their Origins\nWeek 7: Content Farms\nWeek 8: Echo Chambers and Word-of-Mouth Marketing\nWeek 9: Tools and Methods for Fact-Checking\nWeek 10: Netizens and Keyboard Warriors: Unruly Anonymous Justice\nWeek 11: Geopolitics and Information Warfare\nWeek 12: Live Streaming, Influencers, and Memes\nWeek 13: Should Digital Platforms Be Regulated, and How?\nWeek 14: Public Media and High-Quality Media\nWeek 15: Final Project Presentation\nWeek 16: Final Project Presentation"}, "textbook": {"ch": "王維菁、林玉鵬、王俐容(2022)，《AI時代的數位傳播素養教育》，台北：五南出版。\n陳炳宏、柯舜智(2021)，《媒體與資訊素養》，台北：五南出版社。\nManfred Theisen ，王榮輝譯(2019)，《過濾氣泡、假新聞與說謊媒體：我們如何避免被操弄？有自覺使用媒體的第一步》，台北：麥田出版。\nSinal Aral (2021)，《宣傳機器：注意力是貨幣，人人都是數位市場商人》，台北：天下文化。\nTim Wu，黃庭敏譯(2018)，《注意力商人：他們如何操弄人心？揭密媒體、廣告、群眾的角力戰》，台北：天下出版社。\nKaroline Kuhla，顏徽玲譯(2020)，《假新聞》，台北：平安文化。\nJennifer LaGarde and Darren Hudgins，羅世宏、羅敬文合譯 (2020)，《假新聞教戰手冊：怎麼教媒體素養與批判思考》，台北：五南出版。\n每日新聞採訪團隊，(2022)，《失控的匿名正義》(日文翻譯中文)，台北：寶鼎出版。\n劉致昕(2021)，《真相製造：從聖戰士媽媽、極權政府、網軍教練、境外勢力、打假部隊、內容農場主人到政府小編》，台北：春山出版社。\n胡元輝、洪貞玲、羅世宏(2021)研究計畫：《台灣如何對抗不實訊息？跨部門的治理》\n劉致昕、楊子磊、《報導者團隊》(2022)，《烏克蘭的不可能戰爭：反抗，所以存在》，台北：春山出版社。", "en